<p><b>Samuel Hinga Norman</b> (January 1, 1940 – February 22, 2007) was a Sierra Leonean <a href="/wiki/Politician" title="Politician">politician</a> from the <a href="/wiki/Mende_tribe" title="Mende tribe" class="mw-redirect">Mende tribe</a>. He was the founder and leader of the <a href="/wiki/Civil_Defence_Forces" title="Civil Defence Forces">Civil Defence Forces</a>, commonly known as the <a href="/wiki/Kamajors" title="Kamajors">Kamajors</a>. The Kamajors supported the government of <a href="/wiki/Ahmed_Tejan_Kabbah" title="Ahmed Tejan Kabbah" class="mw-redirect">Ahmed Tejan Kabbah</a> against the <a href="/wiki/Revolutionary_United_Front" title="Revolutionary United Front">Revolutionary United Front</a>(RUF), which was led by <a href="/wiki/Foday_Sankoh" title="Foday Sankoh">Foday Sankoh</a>. On 7 March 2003 Hinga Norman was indicted by the <a href="/wiki/Special_Court_for_Sierra_Leone" title="Special Court for Sierra Leone">Special Court for Sierra Leone</a> for war crimes and crimes against humanity. He died on 22 February 2007 in <a href="/wiki/Dakar" title="Dakar">Dakar</a>, <a href="/wiki/Senegal" title="Senegal">Senegal</a> while undergoing <a href="/wiki/Medical_treatment" title="Medical treatment" class="mw-redirect">medical treatment</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
